Advance a theoretical inquiry on causation from a functional and contextual perspective, considering as relata \ul states\ulnone , \ul events\ulnone , and \ul processes\ulnone  (following Galton). The paper assumes an artefact-oriented interpretation of causation and function (device ontology), although the concept of functions aims to be general, including both biological and artificial functions. As the notion of function is connected to the one of goal, the paper includes goal-based observations (\'93a state to be achieved\'94 [p. 9]), and context-oriented.\
\
Toyoshima et al. conceptualise the causal relationship named 
\f2\i achieve
\f1\i0  (and its counterpart 
\f2\i prevents
\f1\i0 ) and highlight the role of \ul states\ulnone  in causal realisations in a \ul state-mediated relationship\ulnone  using 
\f2\i allows
\f1\i0  (and\
