\f0\b \cf0 \
2. IC connections
\f1\b0 \
\cf2 *IC theory goes beyond a canonical approach to causal relation(ship)s, e.g. assuming a qualitative, expert-based perspectives that accounts for uncertainty. Yet it seems that almost all the aforementioned analyses refer to a canonical approach to causal relation(ship)s (only the UFO-based work includes the notion of likelihood).\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \
In IC, classes of Hazards, Exposure, etc are captures, therefore I assume that the connections are also types. Thus in \'93Heavy Precipitation Leads to Flood\'94 the expression aims to be general. Let\'92s say that when there is a flood there might have been an heavy precipitation event, although there are other possible causes of flood (e.g. failure of dams or large amount of snowmelt)*\cf2 to be decided.\cf4  Generally speaking, I would maintain the assumption that the relata of causal relation(ship)s are perdurants, such as events and processes, as it aligns with several works in the literature.\'a0Instead properties (i.e. qualities in DOLCE) are mediators in the causal relation(ship). \cf2 The philosophical literature disagrees that only so-called perdurants (note on the note: the article actually refers to event tokens!) are the relata of causal relation(ship), see: https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/causation-metaphysics/ An alternative is to consider facts as causal relata in this way it is possible to model 
\f2\i \cf2 absence
\f1\i0 \cf2  and 
\f2\i \cf2 omission
\f1\i0 \cf2  as causal force. yet we do not have \cf2 \ul \ulc2 facts\cf2 \ulnone  in DOLCE (yet \cf2 \ul \ulc2 situations\cf2 \ulnone  in UFO could help here). I think that sometimes in climate change risk absence of x can \'93cause\'94 the occurrence of an event, this is the case for several mismanagement and planning. Perhaps we can use event type (pattern)? \
\cf4 For this theory we could have causal relation(ship) that are binary (case and effect) and ternary, the cause, the effect and the mediator. In a similar fashion also Mitigates could be ternary.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Hazards in the IC are sometimes variables associated to events (e.g. frequency, degree). Thus those entities, i.e. variables, seem to play a role in the causal and causal-like relation(ship)s. We could consider those variables as quality (i.e. observable property) associated with events. This would be a slightly more complex patter in which we have a property (P), an event (e) and a time (t).\cf2  \cf4 We could also add a value following the formalisation of qualities in DOLCE.\cf2 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f6\i\b \cf0 1) Leads to
\f1\i0\b0 \
\
\'93Hazards function as the initiating factor in the impact chain. They can trigger both hazards and direct impacts. For instance, torrential rain may trigger landslides, which can damage infrastructure.\'94\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Leads to
\f1\i0  is the only \'93genuine\'94 causal relation between types of perdurants that connects as relata:\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Hazard, Hazard \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Hazard, Impact \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Impact, Impact \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
LeadsTo(x, y) -> (Hazard(x) AND (Hazard(y) OR Impact(y))) OR (Impact(x) AND Impact(y))\
\
This connection is not mediated by any properties, is direct and \'93positive\'94 (i.e. not preventative), and signifies both initiations 
\f2\i a la
\f1\i0  Galton and proper cause.\
\
\cf2 *This relation could be irreflexive, but I feel that in some cases we might have symmetric relations (see compound hazards)\
\cf0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f6\i\b \cf0 2) Affects
\f1\i0\b0 \
\
\'93Lack of land ownership (vulnerability) affects the disruption of agricultural livelihoods in a flood (impact).\'94\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Affects
\f1\i0  is a property mediated connection (PMC), following the characterisation of Toyoshima et al. and inspired by Galton. Thus 
\f2\i Affects
\f1\i0  is not a proper causal relation between types, but rather a causal-like relation in which 1 or more conditions set the stage for an Impact or Risk. The relata of 
\f2\i Allows
\f1\i0  are indeed:\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Vulnerability, Impact/Risk  \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Affects(x, y)  -> (Vulnerability(x) AND (Impact(y) OR Risk(y))\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Affects
\f1\i0  is also direct and \'93positive\'94 and, because of its mediation role, does not generate change by itself, it rather constitute a condition for which an effect can be realised.\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
